Adjust rack to top position and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{12%ounce} on a diagonal into ½-inch-thick pieces. Toss on one side of a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack for ~{10%minutes} (you'll add more to the sheet then).

Meanwhile, in a #small pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{3/4%cup}, 1¼ cups water, and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low.

Cook, covered, until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, trim @green beans{6%ounce} if necessary. Trim and thinly slice @button mushrooms{8%ounce} (skip if your mushrooms are pre-sliced!). Peel and mince or grate @ginger{1%thumb} until you have 1 tsp. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2%unit}, separating whites from greens.

Once carrots have roasted 10 minutes, remove baking sheet from oven. Carefully toss green beans on empty side of sheet with a drizzle of oil, salt, and pepper.

Return sheet to top rack and roast until veggies are lightly browned and tender, ~{12-15%minutes}.

Rinse @shrimp{10%ounce} under cold water; pat dry with #paper towels{}. Season shrimp all over with salt and pepper. Heat a large drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Once pan is hot, add shrimp and cook, stirring occasionally, until opaque and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

> Shrimp are fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.

== Firecracker Sauce ==

In a #small bowl{}, combine @vegan mayo{4%tablespoon}, @Sriracha{1%teaspoon} (use less if you prefer less heat), @sweet soy glaze{1%TBSP}, @rice wine vinegar{1%tsp}, and @sugar{1/2%tsp}.

Add water 1 tsp at a time until sauce reaches a drizzling consistency. Taste and season with salt and pepper. Set aside until ready to serve.

> Be sure to measure the vinegar—we sent more!

== Sautéed Mushrooms ==

Use pan used for shrimp here. Heat a large drizzle of oil in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add mushrooms; cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and slightly crispy, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Reduce heat to medium; stir in minced ginger, scallion whites, @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, and a drizzle of oil. Cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Remove pan from heat and stir in remaining @sweet soy glaze{3%tablespoon} until mushrooms are evenly coated. Cover to keep warm.

== To Serve ==

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; season with salt and pepper.

Divide rice between #bowls{}; top with carrots, green beans, and mushrooms in separate sections. Drizzle bowls with firecracker sauce and garnish with scallion greens and @sesame seeds{1%tablespoon}. Serve.

> Serve shrimp atop bowls.